Sentencas: Recent results on solid oxide fuel cells with Ni/YSZ and Ni/GDC anodes reveal a mechanism for permanent performance degradation due to hydrogen sulfide exposure.
Titulo: Mechanism for SOFC anode degradation from hydrogen sulfide exposure

Sentencas: Our results confirm the temporary performance decline observed by others but also reveal a mechanism for the long term permanent degradation.
Titulo: Mechanism for SOFC anode degradation from hydrogen sulfide exposure

Sentencas: we find that hydrogen sulfide leads to nickel migration and depletion in the anode, thereby compromising electrical conductivity and cell performance.
Titulo: Mechanism for SOFC anode degradation from hydrogen sulfide exposure
